10 AN ACT
11 RELATING TO THE PUBLIC PEACE, HEALTH, SAFETY AND WELFARE;
12 AMENDING AND ENACTING SECTIONS OF THE MEDICAL PRACTICE ACT TO
13 GIVE THE NEW MEXICO MEDICAL BOARD NEW DUTIES AND POWERS;
14 PROHIBITING THE NEW MEXICO MEDICAL BOARD FROM RESTRICTING THE
15 ABILITY OF A LICENSEE TO ADVERTISE THE LICENSEE'S SERVICES;
16 PROVIDING REQUIREMENTS FOR COMPLAINTS AND INVESTIGATIONS
17 AGAINST HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS LICENSED BY THE NEW MEXICO
18 MEDICAL BOARD.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
21 SECTION 1. A new section of the Medical Practice Act is
22 enacted to read:
23 "[NEW MATERIAL] ADVERTISING AND COMPETITIVE BIDDING.--
24 A. The board shall not restrict the ability of a
25 licensee to advertise the licensee's services except to
