13 SECTION 2. A new section of the Medical Practice Act is
14 enacted to read:
15 "[NEW MATERIAL] INFORMATION REQUIRED TO BE PROVIDED TO
16 LICENSEES.--Each time a licensee obtains or renews a license,
17 the board shall provide the licensee with information on:
18 A. best practices for prescribing and dispensing
19 pain medications;
20 B. the risks and signs of substance use disorder
21 for persons who are prescribed prescription pain medications;
22 C. best practices for responding to an overdose of
23 prescription pain medications; and
24 D. how to contact poison control resources in
emergency situations."
